  • Method Details

    • generateClass

      private void generateClass(Class<?> token, BufferedWriter writer) throws IOException
      Generates and writes code of class implementing a given interface token through the specified BufferedWriter.

      The generated code consists of two parts: header and body.

      Parameters:
      token - Class specifies the interface to be implemented
      writer - BufferedWriter to which the generated class is written
      Throws:
      IOException - if an error occurs during writing

    • generateClassHeader

      private void generateClassHeader(Class<?> token, BufferedWriter writer) throws IOException
      Generates and writes header of class-implementation through the specified BufferedWriter.

      The header contains information about package of generated class. Package name is same as the package name of token. If it is unnamed, the package record is not generated.

      Parameters:
      token - Class specifies the interface to be implemented
      writer - BufferedWriter to which the generated class is written
      Throws:
      IOException - if an error occurs during writing

    • generateClassBody

      private void generateClassBody(Class<?> token, BufferedWriter writer) throws IOException
      Generates and writes the code of class-implementation itself with all methods through the specified BufferedWriter.

      Generated code contains a record that the class is public and implements the interface specified by the token. Next, all the methods declared in the interface generated by the generateMethod(Method, BufferedWriter) recorded.

      Parameters:
      token - Class specifies the interface to be implemented
      writer - BufferedWriter to which the generated class is written
      Throws:
      IOException - if an error occurs during writing

    • generateMethod

      private void generateMethod(Method method, BufferedWriter writer) throws IOException
      Generates and writes code of a method through the specified BufferedWriter.

      The generated method is non-abstract. Its parameters, return type and thrown exceptions are the same as the method and defined by getParameters(Parameter[]), getExceptions(Class[]) and .

      Parameters:
      method - whose implementation is generated
      writer - BufferedWriter to which the generated class is written
      Throws:
      IOException - if an error occurs during writing

    • getExceptions

      private String getExceptions(Class<?>[] exceptions)
      Generates a part of the method code describing the exceptions it throws as string.

      Return empty string if exceptions is empty. Otherwise, it returns a string containing the throws keyword and a list of thrown exceptions separated by a comma and a space.

      Parameters:
      exceptions - list of Class specifying thrown exceptions
      Returns:
      String describing the thrown exceptions

      Returns:

      private String getDefaultValue(Class<?> token)

    • implement

      public void implement(Class<?> token, Path root) throws ImplerException
      Description copied from interface: Impler
      Produces code implementing class or interface specified by provided token.

      Generated class' name should be the same as the class name of the type token with Impl suffix added. Generated source code should be placed in the correct subdirectory of the specified root directory and have correct file name. For example, the implementation of the interface List should go to $root/java/util/ListImpl.java

      Specified by:
      implement in interface Impler
      Parameters:
      token - type token to create implementation for.
      root - root directory.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - when implementation cannot be generated.

    • implementJar

      public void implementJar(Class<?> token, Path jarFile) throws ImplerException
      Description copied from interface: JarImpler
      Produces .jar file implementing class or interface specified by provided token.

      Generated class' name should be the same as the class name of the type token with Impl suffix added.

      Specified by:
      implementJar in interface JarImpler
      Parameters:
      token - type token to create implementation for.
      jarFile - target .jar file.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - when implementation cannot be generated.

    • main

      public static void main(String[] args)
      Provides console interface for Implementor. Calls implement(Class, Path) or implementJar(Class, Path) based on number of arguments passed.

      If the first argument is "-jar", calls implementJar(Class, Path), else calls implement(Class, Path). The next two arguments define the class whose implementation is generated and the directory where it should be placed.

      If the passed arguments o not match the description above, prints an error message.

      Parameters:
      args - String array of arguments.
